---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import ThinnerContent from "../../components/ThinnerContent.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import axway from "../../assets/axway.svg";
import Back from "../../components/Back.astro";

const title = "Axway — Global Brand System";
---

<Base title={title}>
  <ThinnerContent>
    <section class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="font-heading font-bold text-4xl sm:text-5xl my-8">{title}</h1>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-12 mb-8 flex items-center justify-center border border-stone-100">
        <Image src={axway} alt="Axway" class="max-w-sm w-full" />
      </div>

      <p class="mb-6">
        Axway is a global enterprise technology company specializing in API management and secure data exchange. I was brought in to bring visual consistency to a product suite that had grown through acquisition — multiple customer-facing systems, each built on a different framework, each looking like a different company.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6">
        The core challenge was that Axway's customer-facing products had grown through acquisition — several support systems and portals built on different frameworks, each with its own visual language. I unified the branding across all of them, starting with a consistent login screen and navigation header that established a shared identity regardless of what was running underneath. That single throughline brought coherence to a fragmented product experience.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6">
        The work required buy-in from multiple product teams, each with their own codebase and priorities — so the solution had to be practical to implement, not just visually correct.
      </p>
    </section>
    <Back next="/work/fastpencil" />
  </ThinnerContent>
</Base>
